---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Welcome! - J. Allan MacDonald"
  description="Website's online and Pointless Magical Relics is available on Kindle!"
  currentPath="/posts/"
>
  <article class="card" style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;" data-animate>
    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);">
      <span class="eyebrow">March 31, 2025</span>
      <h1 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome!</h1>
    </header>

    <p>Website's online and one book is available on Kindle!</p>

    <p>
      <a href="https://amzn.to/4iRyP6Q" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Pointless Magical Relics
      </a>
      is available for Amazon Kindle now.
    </p>

    <div style="text-align: center; margin: var(--space-lg) 0;">
      <a href="https://amzn.to/4iRyP6Q" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="book-cover" style="display: inline-block; max-width: 260px;">
        <img
          src="/assets/pointless-magical-relics-kindle-cover.jpg"
          alt="Pointless Magical Relics Cover"
          width="260"
          height="390"
          style="border-radius: var(--radius-sm);"
        />
      </a>
    </div>

    <p>
      In <em>Pointless Magical Relics</em>, J. Allan MacDonald conjures an enchanting urban fantasy
      beginning in a quiet Seattle bookstore.
    </p>

    <p>
      Jen Winslow, a young clerk with a knack for noticing the odd, thought her days were destined
      to be forgettable—until an unremarkable old book draws the attention of two very different
      strangers: a familiar customer and a man who shouldn't be memorable at all.
    </p>

    <p>
      As tension coils between the shelves and the weight of the unseen presses in, Jen finds herself
      drawn into a hidden world of relics, secrets, and subtle magic. What begins as a quiet curiosity
      spirals into something far stranger, where the line between coincidence and fate begins to blur.
    </p>

    <p>
      With wry humour, creeping suspense, and just a hint of the uncanny, MacDonald invites readers to
      look closer at the objects we overlook—and the people who never quite belong.
    </p>

    <footer style="margin-top: var(--space-lg); padding-top: var(--space-md); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
      <a href="/posts/">← Back to posts</a>
    </footer>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
